<div class="task">
    <h2>Task 1</h2>
    <p>Create a Todo List.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Create it using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</li>
        <li>The web app should have all working functionality</li>
        <li>Implement good designs using CSS</li>
        <li>After completing the project, deploy it on GitHub.</li>
        <li>Host it on Netlify or some other hosting platform</li>
        <li>Submit the link of the hosted website and GitHub repository on the below submission form</li>
        <li>Marks: 20/100</li>
        <li>Ideal time required: 1 day</li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
    <h2>Task 2</h2>
    <p>Create an IMDB clone.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>The clone should have minimal basic features of IMDB like login and signup, home page, searching movies, displaying all the movie details with rating, and also add to wishlist feature.</li>
        <li>The web app should have a good design, and you can also give it your own touch</li>
        <li>Use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript frameworks to make the clone, and for the database, you can use MongoDB</li>
        <li>Use available APIs to fetch movie data according to the search bar (hint: use APIs from Rapid API)</li>
        <li>After completing the project, deploy it on GitHub.</li>
        <li>Host it on Netlify or some other hosting platform</li>
        <li>Submit the link of the hosted website and GitHub repository on the below submission form</li>
        <li>Marks: 30/100</li>
        <li>Ideal Time Required: 3 days</li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="task">
    <h2>Task 3</h2>
    <p>Netflix Clone in React.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Create a Netflix clone; the frontend should be in React, and for the backend, use Firebase</li>
        <li>The Netflix clone should have visually appealing designs, and you can also give it your own touch</li>
        <li>Implement only the basic functionality of Netflix like the home page, search bar, sign-in page, sign-up page, browse page, and movie player page</li>
        <li>After completing the project, deploy it on GitHub.</li>
        <li>Host it on Netlify or some other hosting platform</li>
        <li>Submit the link of the hosted website and GitHub repository on the below submission form</li>
        <li>Max Marks: 50/100</li>
    </ul>
</div>
